FBIS4-41553 "drsov123_b_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 25 Jun 1994 RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Income Tax Proposed To Fund War on Crime Income Tax Proposed To Fund War on Crime MK2506110094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 25 Jun 94 p 1 MK2506110094 Moscow SEGODNYA Russian BFN [POSTFACTUM report: "Russian Federation Finance Ministry Proposes Special Tax To Combat Crime"] [Text] The Russian Federation Finance Ministry has forwarded to the government and the Security Council a proposal to introduce a special personal income tax to finance the federal crime fighting program. The proposed maximum rate of the tax is 3 percent. It has been suggested not to tax citizens' monthly incomes below 70,000 rubles.
